parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
grinding or scraping noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to stall or run out of fuel, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect readings
often showing a quarter tank of fuel when the tank is empty
or vice versa. The vehicle may stall or shut down without warning
and the fuel gauge may not accurately reflect the fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays an incorrect fuel level
often showing a quarter of a tank remaining when the tank is actually empty
the fuel gauge fails to illuminate the low fuel warning light
the vehicle stalls or loses power without warning.
